<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Ability to solo effectively. Does this class possess the tools to solo with an acceptable experience/downtime ratio to make soloing a viable option for experience gain?<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Acceptable in comparision to what? A necro or a warrior?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Group contribution- Does this class have a variety of skills which make it valuable in a group?<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
You need a question about stackability in groups too.<br>
Clerics and chanters are VERY usefull to a group and sometimes even needed, but more than one is really not needed and usually cause problems with misunderstanding of tasks to do in the group.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Raid contribution-Does this class have a variety of skills which make it valuable in a<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
You also need a stackability question for raids.<br>
The first 2 warriors really add some tanking ability, but the next ones are just lousy damage dealers.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Equipment-Does this class have a good variety of equipment available to enhance it’s specific abilities?<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Variety is one thing availability is another.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Overall-Is this class properly balanced?<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Compared to what? A necro or a monk?<br>
You need to define this a bit more clearly, like balanced to other offensive classes, defensive classes, casters, healers, robe wearers, plate wearers and so on.<br>
<br>
<br>
In general all the questions can mean quite different things when one is looking at the level of the player. Clerics with complete heal gets a real boost and from then on will really like a good addition to a group.<br>
Clerics at level 56 gets Yaulp 5 and the summoned proc hammer, which means they can suddenly solo somewhat well, compared to a 55 cleric that fears anything beating on him.<br>
A question about the current level of the toon might be a good idea here.<br>
